. Consistent with other liberating perspectives, it outs God from heteronormative closets and restores human sexuality as a resource for theology. This outing of divine queerness—that is, the ineffability of divine life—helps to align reflections on the mystery of God with the faith experiences of queer Catholics. By engaging Juan de la Cruz through queer Latinx eyes, Miguel Díaz continues the objective of this series to disrupt the cartography of theology latinamente.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aHispanic American theology. 0aMysticism in literature. 0aQueer theology. 0aTheology in literature. 0aTrinity in literature. 4aLGBTQ Studies. 4aLatinx Studies. 4aTheology. 7aRELIGION / Christian Theology / Systematic.2bisacsh  aGod.  aLGBTQ+.  aLiving Flame of Love.  aLlama de Amor Viva.  aMystery of God.  aQueer.  aSan Juan de la Cruz.  aTrinity.  aapophatic.  acataphatic.  adark night.  adesire.  aecstasis, St. John of the Cross.  amysticism.  anoche oscura.  aperichoresis.  asanjuanistamente.  aselfcommunication.  asexuality.  aun no sé qué.1 aDíaz, Miguel H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNanko-Fernández, Carmen M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRiebe-Estrella, Gary, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2022 Englishz978311099454408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2022z9783110994537oZDB-23-DGF08iTitle